    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                
                <!-- Page 1 -->
                <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.4816_1.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <lb/>Hotel Terminus,
                        <lb/><placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2977246">St Raphael</placeName>,
                        <lb/>Côte d’Azur,
                        <lb/><placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/3017382">France</placeName>.
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>
                        <lb/>My dear <persName ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/54148778">Thomas Hardy</persName>,
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>
                    <lb/>Of course your last
                    <lb/>note does not, did not require
                    <lb/>an answer – any more than my
                    <lb/>rather bold envoy of books needed
                    <lb/>acknowledgement – only it is
                    <lb/>so specially difficult to get any
                    <lb/>criticism whatever of any other aspects
                    <lb/>than the malice engendered by stupidity –
                    <lb/>of the hurried hack work of poor
                    <lb/>devils who have to write reviews –
                    <lb/>that if you have by any chance
                    <lb/>looked at the wretched brochures
                    <lb/>again and found any specific
                    <lb/>merit or demerit it would be
                </p>
                
                <!-- Page 2 -->
                <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.4816_3.jpg"/>
                
                <p>
                    <lb/>no inconsiderable kindness to send one
                    <lb/>word. – not a politeness, –
                    <lb/>the perplexity is confirmed. The melancholy
                    <lb/>is there – one tries to comfort oneself
                    <lb/>with the argument that the qualities
                    <lb/>are inherent in the subject matter. –
                    <lb/>It is, perhaps, my “un–English” to
                    <lb/>regard literature as a “mystery”,
                    <lb/>a druidic guild, in which one
                    <lb/>receives at least a few orders,
                    <lb/>a few prohibitions from the generation
                    <lb/>older, – recognizes the fact that the
                    <lb/>stuff in question may have the
                    <lb/>supreme fault of being “merely uninteresting” –
                    <lb/>in which case no criticism is
                    <lb/>possible – &amp; there is no remedy
                    <lb/>but the chance of doing better next time.
                </p>
                
                <!-- Page 3 -->
                <pb n="3" facs="uoedh_hl_h.4816_5.jpg"/>
                
                <p>
                    <lb/>I don’t know that I have any other
                    <lb/>excuse to offer for writing this note.
                    <lb/>I was very much surprised
                    <lb/>that you had
                    <lb/>heard of me at all – as indicated
                    <lb/>in your first reply to my importunities
                    <lb/>on behalf of the <hi>The Dial</hi>.
                    <lb/>I don’t think mere praise is any
                    <lb/>good – I know where I can get it,
                    <lb/>&amp; just what wrong reasons will lead
                    <lb/>one or two eminent contemporaries
                    <lb/>to like or tolerate certain passages.
                    <lb/>Forgive me if I blurt out
                    <lb/>this demand for more frankness
                    <lb/>than anything, save perhaps a
                    <lb/>lifelong friendship, can engender
                    <lb/>between two individuals,
                    <lb/><signed><persName ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/44300634">Ezra Pound</persName></signed>.
                </p>
                
                <!-- Page 4 -->
                <pb n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.4816_7.jpg"/>
                
                <p>
                    <lb/>And also concede that I know
                    <lb/>how much right you have to your
                    <lb/>quiet – and how little one ought
                    <lb/>to break in upon it – and
                    <lb/>in the end don’t answer
                    <lb/>this, if the whole subject bores you
                    <lb/>unspeakably.
                    <lb/>cordially
                    <lb/>E. P.
                </p>
                
                <p>
                    <lb/>permanent address
                    <lb/>5 Holland Place
                    <lb/>Chambers,
                    <lb/><placeName ref="https://www.geonames.org/2643743">London</placeName> W.8.
                </p>
                
            </div>
        </body>
